Class BSTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • BSTree<T>

  • public class BSTree<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
    This is binary search tree class over items of type T. It is roughly along the lines of the class described in section 6.2 of Open Data Structures. The one big change is that this class uses a sentinel node ANCHOR, where
    • ANCHOR.left = the actual root of the tree
    • ANCHOR.parent = ANCHOR.right = ANCHOR.data = null
    We compare data fields via the method compare below where we arrange that null acts like +∞, so that the ANCHOR node is the rightmost/largest node in the (extended) tree.
